Subject: [PATCH] SwiftBuild: derive Android -tools-directory from discovered NDK

For an Android cross-link, swiftc drives the link. To find the linker it
honors -tools-directory: if that directory contains a clang, swiftc uses it
as the link driver (GenericUnixToolchain+LinkerSupport.swift). When no usable
-tools-directory is given, swiftc falls back to the host clang, which adds the
host toolchain's own lib directory to the link and drags host x86_64
libc++/libunwind onto the aarch64 link:

    ld.lld: error: <host>/lib/libunwind.a(...) is incompatible with aarch64linux

The Android Swift SDK supplies -tools-directory only indirectly, through the
bundle's swift-toolset.json `rootPath` (translated to -tools-directory by the
android-preserve-swift-sdk-toolsets patch). That path points at the bundle's
ndk-toolchain/bin, which is populated from the local NDK by a post-install
setup step. If that step is skipped the directory is empty, swiftc finds no
clang there, and the host clang leak above occurs — even though the SDK plugin
already discovered the NDK and is passing its sysroot, clang resource dir, and
ld.lld.

Make the discovered NDK the single source of truth for the tool path: inject
-tools-directory <ndk>/bin into OTHER_SWIFT_FLAGS and OTHER_LDFLAGS directly in
the Android platform plugin, alongside the SYSROOT / CLANG_RESOURCE_DIR /
ALTERNATE_LINKER_PATH it already derives from the same NDK. Correctness no
longer depends on the SDK bundle's ndk-toolchain/bin being set up.

Sentinel: NUCLEUS_SWIFT_BUILD_ANDROID_NDK_TOOLS_DIRECTORY

diff --git a/Sources/SWBAndroidPlatform/Plugin.swift b/Sources/SWBAndroidPlatform/Plugin.swift
index 7e1dc23e..8a2b1c40 100644
--- a/Sources/SWBAndroidPlatform/Plugin.swift
+++ b/Sources/SWBAndroidPlatform/Plugin.swift
@@ -185,16 +185,37 @@ struct AndroidPlatformExtension: PlatformInfoExtension {

 // Properties applied to the builtin NDK-only SDK as well as Swift SDKs
 fileprivate func androidSDKAdditionalCustomProperties(ndk: AndroidSDK.NDK, hostOS: OperatingSystem) -> [String: PropertyListItem] {
-    [
+    // NUCLEUS_SWIFT_BUILD_ANDROID_NDK_TOOLS_DIRECTORY:
+    // Derive -tools-directory from the discovered NDK so that swiftc, when it
+    // drives the link, resolves the NDK clang instead of falling back to the
+    // host clang. The host clang adds its own lib directory to the link, which
+    // leaks host x86_64 libc++/libunwind onto the Android (aarch64) link and
+    // fails with "incompatible with aarch64linux". This makes the discovered
+    // NDK the single source of truth for the tool path — matching how SYSROOT,
+    // CLANG_RESOURCE_DIR, and ALTERNATE_LINKER_PATH are already derived here —
+    // so correctness no longer depends on a post-install setup step populating
+    // the SDK bundle's ndk-toolchain/bin (a toolset rootPath).
+    let ndkToolsDirectory = ndk.toolchainPath.path.join("bin").str
+    return [
         // Unlike most platforms, the Android version goes on the environment field rather than the system field
         // FIXME: Make this configurable in a better way so we don't need to push build settings at the SDK definition level
         "SWIFT_TARGET_TRIPLE": .plString("$(CURRENT_ARCH)-unknown-$(SWIFT_PLATFORM_TARGET_PREFIX)$(LLVM_TARGET_TRIPLE_SUFFIX)"),
         "LLVM_TARGET_TRIPLE_OS_VERSION": .plString("$(SWIFT_PLATFORM_TARGET_PREFIX)"),
         "LLVM_TARGET_TRIPLE_SUFFIX": .plString("-android$(SWIFT_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET)"),

+        // Resolve the NDK clang/ld as the swiftc tools directory for both
+        // compilation and swiftc-driven linking.
+        "OTHER_SWIFT_FLAGS": .plArray([
+            .plString("$(inherited)"),
+            .plString("-tools-directory"),
+            .plString(ndkToolsDirectory)
+        ]),
+
         // Android NDK r28+ defaults to 16kb page sizes for aarch64 and x86_64.
         "OTHER_LDFLAGS[arch=aarch64]": .plArray([
             .plString("$(inherited)"),
+            .plString("-tools-directory"),
+            .plString(ndkToolsDirectory),
             .plString("-Xlinker"),
             .plString("-z"),
             .plString("-Xlinker"),
@@ -202,6 +223,8 @@ fileprivate func androidSDKAdditionalCustomProperties(ndk: AndroidSDK.NDK, hostO
         ]),
         "OTHER_LDFLAGS[arch=x86_64]": .plArray([
             .plString("$(inherited)"),
+            .plString("-tools-directory"),
+            .plString(ndkToolsDirectory),
             .plString("-Xlinker"),
             .plString("-z"),
             .plString("-Xlinker"),
